function.name: Copy
function.desc: Creates a copy of this object.

function.name: Set
function.desc: Changes the color components to the specified values.

function.name: Lerp
function.desc: Linearly interpolates between this color and the given color ''c'' by the specified ''factor''.

function.name: ToVector4
function.desc: Converts this color to a [pragma:ref]math.Vector4[/pragma:ref] and divides all components by 255. If you don't need the alpha-component, you can use [pragma:ref]util.Color:ToVector[/pragma:ref] instead.

function.name: ToVector
function.desc: Converts this color to a [pragma:ref]math.Vector[/pragma:ref] and divides all components by 255. The alpha-component will be lost, to keep it, use [pragma:ref]util.Color:ToVector4[/pragma:ref].

function.name: operator/
function.desc: Divides the color by the specified value and returns the result.

function.name: operator*
function.desc: Multiplies the color with the specified value and returns the result.

function.name: operator+
function.desc: Adds the color to the specified value and returns the result.

function.name: operator-
function.desc: Subtracts the specified color from this color and returns the result.

function.name: operator==
function.desc: Compares this color to the specified one and returns ''true'' if they represent the same color.

function.name: tostring
function.desc: Converts the color to a string.
